  "wikitext": "{{Object Infobox\n|name=Scrap\n|image=Scrap Dropped.png\n|icon=Scrap.png\n|stack=40\n|droppedBy = {{pic|32|Teetering Junk Pile}}{{pic|32|Junk Pile}}{{pic|32|Junky Fence}}(25%)<br>{{pic|32|Abandoned Junk}} {{pic|32|Enlightened W.A.R.B.O.T.}} {{pic|48|Scrappy Werepig}}<br>{{pic|32|Cachebox}}{{pic|32|Advanced Cachebox Broken|Cachebox}}({{pic|32|Winona Portrait|Winona}}only)\n|spawnCode = \"wagpunk_bits\"\n}}{{Exclusivity|Don't Starve Together}}\n\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = I bet I could make something incredibly scientific with this.\n|willow = What am I supposed to do with that?\n|wolfgang = Funny metal bits.\n|wendy = Only parts of a greater whole. Just like me.\n|wx78 = HELLO MY BEAUTIES\n|wickerbottom = Where are the instructions?\n|woodie = Some odd bits of metal.\n|maxwell = Someone should collect this bric-à-brac and put it to use.\n|wigfrid = What use wöuld a warriör have för such leavings?\n|webber = We love puzzles!\n|winona = Don't let its looks fool you, these are some high-quality parts!\n|warly = Ingredients for some sort of machine?\n|wortox = I'll have to settle for these scraps of metal.\n|wormwood = Robot buildy bits?\n|wurt = Blegh. Not food.\n|walter = Oooh, nice! Wonder what we can do with these.\n|wanda = Gears and wires and sprockets, oh my!\n|choose = wanda\n}}\n\n'''Scrap''' is an [[Item]] exclusive to ''[[Don't Starve Together]]'', introduced in ''[[From Beyond]]''. It can be obtained by rummaging through [[Junk Pile]]s or destroying [[Junky Fence]] with a 25% chance. After [[Lunar Rift]]s are activated, it can also be obtained by hammering [[Abandoned Junk]] which appear in [[Junk Yard]] (if [[Scrappy Werepig]] is not alive).\n\nScrap is used to craft and upgrade the [[Lunar Siphonator]]. After the activation of Lunar Rifts, it can be used to craft the [[Auto-Mat-O-Chanic]], [[W.A.R.B.I.S. Head Gear]], and [[W.A.R.B.I.S. Armor]] after learning the corresponding rare [[Blueprint]]s which dropped from Abandoned Junk and Scrappy Werepig.\n\nLike [[Gears]], repairing [[Broken Clockworks]] in the Ruins with 3 Scraps will spawn a friendly damaged chess monster ([[Damaged Bishop]], [[Damaged Knight]], or [[Damaged Rook]]).\n\n== {{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1= Scrap\n|count1= 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result= Scrap Wall\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = blueprint_(rare)\n|item1 = Scrap\n|item2 = Electrical Doodad/DST\n|result = Auto-Mat-O-Chanic\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = blueprint_(rare)\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1= 4\n|item2 = Moongleam\n|count2= 5\n|item3= Electrical Doodad/DST\n|count3= 2\n|result = Lunar Siphonator\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = blueprint_(rare)\n|item3= Enlightened Shard\n|count3= 1\n|item2= Electrical Doodad/DST\n|count2= 3\n|item1= Scrap\n|count1= 8\n|result= W.A.R.B.I.S. Head Gear\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = blueprint_(rare)\n|item3= Enlightened Shard\n|count3= 1\n|item2= Electrical Doodad/DST\n|count2= 3\n|item1= Scrap\n|count1= 8\n|result= W.A.R.B.I.S. Armor\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = blueprint_(rare)\n|item3= Enlightened Shard\n|count3= 1\n|item2= Pure Brilliance\n|count2= 2\n|item1= Scrap\n|count1= 4\n|result= Elastispacer\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 6\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 6\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n|result = T.I.N.G.L.E. Node\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|item2 = Cut Stone/DST\n|result = Substrate Extrapolator\n|resultcount = 4\n|tool = Notional Fabricator\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Thulecite Bug Net\n|result = Phasmo-Encapsulator\n|tool = Notional Fabricator\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|item2 = Cut Stone/DST\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Boards/DST\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Notional Fabricator\n|result = W.A.R.B.O.T. Base Kit\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Cut Stone/DST\n|tool = Notional Fabricator\n|result = W.A.R.B.O.T. Parts\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 2\n|tool = Notional Fabricator\n|result= Static Restrainer\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 5\n|item2 = Electrical Doodad\n|count2 = 2\n|result = B.U.D.D.Y.\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 8\n|item2 = Electrical Doodad/DST\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Doohickey\n|count3 = 3\n|result = W.I.N.bot\n|character = Winona\n|skill = Founder's Keepers I\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Electrical Doodad/DST\n|item3 = Frazzled Wires\n|result = Scrappy Slingshot Frame\n|character = Walter\n|skill = Advanced Frames\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|item2 = Saffron Feather\n|result = Shockscrap Shots\n|resultcount = 20\n|character = Walter\n|skill = Utility Rounds\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 8\n|item2 = Bio Data\n|count2 = 10\n|item3 = Electrical Doodad\n|count3 = 1\n|result = Zaptrocuter\n|skill = Telemechanical Enthusiast I\n|character = WX-78\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Scrap\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Bio Data\n|count2 = 12\n|result = Spectral Transfer Module\n|skill = Lunar Vessel\n|character = WX-78\n}}\n\n== {{pic|32|Prototype}} Tips ==\n\n* Scrap can easily be farmed renewably by periodically going to the [[Junk Yard]] and hammering the [[Junky Fence]]s and [[Abandoned Junk]].\n\n== {{pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Scrap was introduced in the ''[[Host of Horrors]]'' Update.\n* Before the ''[[Scrappy Scavengers]]'' Update, Scrap was not available outside of the Lunar Rifts, and was not used for the Lunar Siphonator.\n* On initial beta release, Scrap could be eaten by [[WX-78/Don't Starve Together|WX-78]]. This was not intended and removed in Update 575729. It has food type [[Food_Type/DST#Gears|Gears]] (Health - 60, Sanity - 50, Hunger - 75)\n\n{{clear}}\n{{Resources}}\n[[vi:Scrap]]\n[[zh:废料]]"
}
